            "answer_text": "I wrote one about 2 years ago. It\u2019s called Turning Tantrums Into Triumphs - The Step-By-Step Guide To Stopping Toddler Tantrums. My daughter started having terrible twos tantrums since she was one year old (yes, she was very advanced that way). There were many opinions on how parents should handle toddler tantrums. but most of them just didn\u2019t sound right to me. To be honest, many of them sounded very mean! For example, many people believe that you should just ignore the child and they\u2019ll stop. From the parents\u2019 perspective, this strategy may \u201cwork\u201d. Tantrums do often stop that way and parents are happy. But I worry about its impact on the child. I didn\u2019t believe that was the best thing to do for the kid and I wanted nothing but the best for my child. I focused on scientific evidence. After much researching, I found a solution that worked very well for us. So I wrote down my findings and hoped to help other parents. I didn\u2019t know whether it would really work for others as well as it worked for my child. Fortunately, feedback has been good and I\u2019m glad some families benefit from it. ",
