                "name": "Elesa Zehndorfer",
                "href": "/profile/Elesa-Zehndorfer"
            },
            "answer_text": "I\u2019m on my third right now - the first focused on a critical introduction to all of the major leadership theories of the last century (a textbook). The second looked at the role of charisma in the global financial crisis, and proposed a synergy between Hyman Minsky's Credit Cycle and Max Weber's charisma (also a textbook-& a case study within it was used as the basis of a journal article). The current one looks at physiological bases of irrational & emotional investing, offering both causes and solutions (my first professional title). I am a huge fan of trying to make complex theory accessible and in making philosophy understandable as it has such an empowering application to all of our lives, so each book considers research concepts and research philosophy in some depth (in particular, the third devotes a large part of a chapter to it). I feature a lot of exciting examples alongside that kind of theory so it is lighter to read. Each book has a lot of expert insights as well, as I like to connect theory with practice. Routledge will have published all three (the third should be released later this year). I always said that after 3 books I could call myself a writer. It's a real dream for me. But I think I need a big break from non fiction titles\u2026the next will be a sci fi or mystery (I have a plot ready for both)\u2026I don't know whether either will get a deal but hey, try your best and enjoy the process\u2026 ",
